%h3= _('HMIS Data Quality 20%')
%p= simple_format(_('HMIS participation and data quality are priorities for TX-601 & HUD. Accurate, complete & timely data is crucial to determine how projects are contributing to ending homelessness.  High quality data is key to understanding what projects are doing and how the CoC & HUD can make informed decisions about the project.'))
.overflow-scroll
  %table.table.table-bordered
    %thead
      %tr
        %th.text-nowrap Performance Criteria
        %th.text-nowrap Purpose & Source of Measurement
        %th.text-nowrap Formula Information
        %th.text-nowrap Performance Calculation
        %th.text-nowrap Scoring
        %th.text-nowrap Total
    %tbody
      %tr
        %th Personal Identifying Information Error Rate
        %th{rowspan: 3}
          To achieve accurate data collection and to satisfy HUD HMIS data requirements, projects must ensure that data entered into the local HMIS system is complete.
          %br
            HUD Data Quality Report; APR Q6a, Q6b, Q6c
        %th

        %td.text-center= f.input :percent_pii_errors, label: false, as: :read_only
        %th.text-nowrap{rowspan: 3}
          .mb-4
            Points: 10
            %br
            0% - 1%
          .mb-4
            Points: 5
            %br
            2% - 5%
          .mb-4
            Points: 0
            %br
            >= 6%
        %td.text-center= @report.pii_errors_score
      %tr
        %th Universal Data Elements Error Rate
        %th

        %td.text-center= f.input :percent_ude_errors, label: false, as: :read_only

        %td.text-center= @report.ude_errors_score
      %tr
        %th Income and Housing Data Quality
        %th

        %td.text-center= f.input :percent_income_and_housing_errors, label: false, as: :read_only

        %td.text-center= @report.income_and_housing_errors_score
